g answers to these questions. Besides being the first detailed description of the prosody of a Central Quechuan language, it provides an in-depth study of the intonational systems and prosodic structures of the two languages and shows that their variation spaces overlap to a large extent, in turns exhibiting or not exhibiting evidence of word stress, pitch accents, lexical pitch accents in loanwords, and head- or edge-prominence.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aIntonation. 4aQuechua-Sprache. 4aSpanisch. 4aSprachtypologie. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / Spanish.2bisacsh  aQuechua.  aSpanish.  aintonation.  alanguage typology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2023 Englishz978311131916208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2023z9783111318240oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831113062470 cprintz978311130364240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783111304595zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111304595zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111304595/original  a978-3-11-131916-2 EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSPb2023  aZDB-23-GOA